    <section class="overview-card">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        What this page contains: This is a container page integrating four assignments (A1‚ÄìA4), each loaded via separate links. Each assignment features its own layout alongside visualisations or interactive elements.
        The unified interface serves merely as an outer framework, with iframes preserving each assignment's native functionality internally.
      </p>
      <p>
        Challenges encountered during merging: Different modules employed distinct HTML, CSS, and JS structures. Directly stacking these would cause conflicts, particularly with interactive charts where layouts would frequently break down,
        even triggering horizontal scrollbars.
      </p>
      <p>
        My solution: Load each assignment in an isolated iframe, keeping all styles and scripts separate. Set overflow-x to hidden on the outer layer to prevent horizontal scrollbars.
        This ensures both secure integration and a clean, visually appealing interface.
        The most challenging assignments to integrate are typically A3 or A4, as they often involve greater interactivity and chart requirements.
      </p>
    </section>

    <h1>IDV Assignment 5 ¬∑ Integrated View</h1>

    <div class="nav">
      <!-- ‰Ωú‰∏öÂØºËà™ÊåâÈíÆ -->
      <button class="nav-btn active" data-src="https://zzz747214260-sudo.github.io/IDV-assignment1/">A1</button>
      <button class="nav-btn" data-src="https://zzz747214260-sudo.github.io/IDV-assignment2/">A2</button>
